00:06:43.640 --> 00:06:45.840
THROUGHOUT OUR STUDY OF ALGEBRA,

00:06:45.840 --> 00:06:49.773
SO LET'S GO AHEAD AND START 
WITH THIS INNERMOST RECTANGLE.

00:06:49.773 --> 00:06:51.640
IF YOU TAKE A LOOK 
AT THE REMAINING SETS HERE,

00:06:51.640 --> 00:06:54.773
WE HAVE NATURAL NUMBERS, 
WHOLE NUMBERS, INTEGERS,

00:06:54.773 --> 00:06:56.873
RATIONAL AND IRRATIONALS.

00:06:56.873 --> 00:06:59.947
WELL, THE NATURAL NUMBERS ARE 1, 
2, 3, OR THE COUNTING NUMBERS.

00:06:59.947 --> 00:07:02.413
THEY WOULD BE THE INNERMOST SET.

00:07:02.413 --> 00:07:03.813
NEXT, THE ONLY DIFFERENCE

00:07:03.813 --> 00:07:06.580
BETWEEN WHOLE NUMBERS 
AND NATURAL NUMBERS

00:07:06.580 --> 00:07:09.347
IS THAT THE SET OF WHOLE NUMBERS 
INCLUDES ZERO.

00:07:09.347 --> 00:07:13.947
SO THAT WOULD BE THE NEXT SET.

00:07:13.947 --> 00:07:15.780
NEXT COMES THE INTEGERS.

00:07:15.780 --> 00:07:18.047
INTEGERS CONSIST 
OF POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE

00:07:18.047 --> 00:07:23.480
NATURAL NUMBERS AND ZERO, SO 
THAT WOULD BE THE NEXT SET.

00:07:23.480 --> 00:07:26.113
AND NOW, WE'RE LEFT 
WITH TWO SETS

00:07:26.113 --> 00:07:27.213
AND THAT'S GOING TO CONSIST

00:07:27.213 --> 00:07:30.247
OF THE RATIONAL 
AND IRRATIONAL NUMBERS.

00:07:30.247 --> 00:07:33.980
NATURAL NUMBERS, WHOLE NUMBERS 
AND INTEGERS ARE RATIONAL,

00:07:33.980 --> 00:07:37.180
SO THEY WOULD BE WITHIN THE SET 
OF RATIONAL NUMBERS

00:07:37.180 --> 00:07:42.447
WHICH LEAVES THIS SET OVER HERE 
TO BE THE IRRATIONAL NUMBERS.

00:07:42.447 --> 00:07:44.480
SO IT IS IMPORTANT TO KNOW HOW 
THE SETS OF NUMBERS

00:07:44.480 --> 00:07:45.980
RELATE TO ONE ANOTHER,

00:07:45.980 --> 00:07:48.447
SO YOU MIGHT CONSIDER 
SKETCHING ONE OF THESE DIAGRAMS

